                    <span>For years, the only intro for RUP was Philippe Kruchten's book. And it was not enough... Then Larman's book came out (the great one, no doubt!), but this book is too much for someone who wants to understand process without going into UML discussions (the main purpose of Larman's book).<BR>"Rational Unified Process Made Easy" finally closes the gap.<BR>Even if you know (or think you know) RUP, it would be a good idea to buy this one.</span>
                  
              
